  "note": "The official 2025/26 Study Scheme publishes a 66-unit Major requirement: 9 Faculty Package units, 30 Required units and 27 Elective units. Students are assigned to either the International Stream or Chinese Native Stream, complete four Stream Courses, three fixed Experiential Learning Courses, two fixed Research Component Courses and nine Major Electives under the published level and subject-area minima. Both Streams are modelled as separate Major/Track identities so local plans remain isolated. This supplement records all 47 CHES-coded courses whose code, title and 3-unit value are explicitly printed in the Study Scheme. The Faculty Package's two-of-many external Arts choices and the International Stream's CLCP/approved CLCC language pools are not included because the Study Scheme publishes their codes but not their official titles; the same omission applies to non-CHES external options. Recommended Year and Term are assigned only where the official course pattern fixes them. This verified coded planning subset does not claim that the omitted external pools or University Core requirements have been completed.",
